{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|な}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref> Possibly [[cognate]] with {{cog|ko|날||[[blade]]}}.

Obsolete in modern Japanese. Only found as an element in compounds.

{{ja-noun|な}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=な|obsolete}} a [[blade]], [[edge]]
#* {{RQ:Man'yōshū|4|616}},<ref>{{R:Man'yōshū 1}}</ref> text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man4Yos.html#616 here]
#*: {{ja-usex|m=劔%大刀 '''名'''惜雲 吾%者%無 君%尓%不相%而 年%之経去礼者|m_kana=つるぎ%たち '''なの'''をしけく も われ%は%なし きみ%に%あはず%て とし%のへぬれば|[[剣%太刀]]'''名'''の惜しけくも我れはなし君に逢はずて年の経ぬれば|つるぎ%たち '''な''' の をしけく も われ は なし きみ に あはずて とし の へぬれば|rom=tsurugitachi '''na''' no oshikeku mo ware wa nashi kimi ni awazute toshi no henureba|I do not even miss precious '''you''', given the years that have passed without meeting with you.}}
#*:: [Note: ''tsurugi tachi'' (“[[sword]]”) is a [[w:Makurakotoba|pillow word]] establishing a poetic association with the following ''na'', literally meaning {{m|en|blade}} or {{m|en|edge}} and alluding to sharpness and importance. This ''na'' could also elliptically mean {{m|en|name}} ({{ja-l|名}} ''na'') or even {{m|en|you}} ({{ja-l|汝}} ''na''), depending on context, based on the homophonic readings.]
